reviews_data.review_text:
I placed an order around 7:15 this morning. I scheduled it to be picked up at 9:30am. I got a text at around 7:30am saying that my order was ready. I got there at 9:30 to pick up my order and asked them when it was made. The lady at the counter said they remade it. Not sure why they made it two hours early but okay, I guess. I get out to my car and my husband double checked his drink. He ordered a caramel frappe with 4 shots of espresso. I understand that adding espresso can make it more liquidy than frozen looking. My concern was that it was completely separated like it had been sitting for 20 minutes. I took it back inside and they remade it. I ordered a hot chocolate with whipped cream and chocolate drizzle. It contained neither of those things and was lukewarm like it had also been sitting for 20 minutes. When I placed my order, it said that it would take 10 minutes to be ready. There is absolutely no reason those drinks should’ve been like that when I scheduled the pick up for a certain time. I will not be returning to this location.

Updating to add that instead of getting a new cup for a fresh drink, she rinsed and reused the same cup I had brought back in.

reviews_data.review_text: My new favorite coffee place! I am partial to almond milk lattes and here they are just right- creamy, not too bitter and just the slightest bit of natural sweetness.

Update:
Went here a couple days ago with my daughter. The hipster vibe was on fire with gentleman behind the counter. Nose ring and all, he had the look. He's on the phone or something, but he's talking into the microphone thing attached to his ear. I figured it was drivetheu. Couldn't be, he's talking too long. Nobody in this shop. We are the only ones. He looks at us and says it will be a minute. He's tooling around with cups, etc. I realize quickly we won't be served anytime soon. We wait, and wait. Then we walk.

The atmosphere as far as the aesthetic of this place is nice. Perhaps I've always been there when the staff seemed weirded out/perplexed that I'm asking questions about the menu, etc. No personality at all. The coffee that I ordered was actually really good. The muffin i always get for my daughter is absolutely delicious. This is why I'm giving 4 stars. It was very expensive compared to other places... but I get it, it's a locally owned shop and I get that. A tip jar at the counter is a great idea, and I usually tip. But when the tip option is on the screen that you are using to pay, it is embarrassing when you don't tip or don't tip a lot. I'm sure they know how much you're tipping. It took a good 10 minutes to get my order. I wasn't in a hurry but I've been here multiple times and it seems to take a while. I do fear that the Starbucks may do some damage to this neat coffee shop. Maybe consider lowering the prices a bit and speeding up the service a bit. Staff personality doesn't bother me as long as service and food is good. I'll still frequent this place but this is review is for consideration of management.
I'm extremely glad I began going to this location for my morning coffee fix. The coffee is great and the service is awesome. Highly recommend!

While I was waiting for my order, I set up my laptop and started waiting, the other employee called out an order so I went over and asked if this was the apple macchiato since it had no label on it and just got a yes. It wasn’t an apple macchiato. So I went over and double checked after a couple minutes of trying to like whatever coffee they gave me (I really hate complaining about orders), the second employee remade it and was really nice about it while the girl just stood there. Now it’s been 15 minutes and I still haven’t received my sandwich, I notice the girl leaves for the day so I walk over to the other employee who was there and asked about it and they pointed to the box on the counter, as I got back to my table and opened it, it was empty. So I went back over and told them how it’s literally just an empty box, they apologized and asked what sandwich I ordered, I ordered the Ham & Swiss. Well turns out the Ham & Swiss was out of stock and the girl never told me and just completely forgot about it? The employee did refund me but I still haven’t received it.
It sucks I had an amazing experience the first time and that’s why I will give them two stars but the second time I really felt neglected and definitely won’t be back
